#Fill empty columns

# Fill numerical columns with mean
for col in df.select_dtypes(include=['float64']).columns:
    df[col].fillna(df[col].mean(), inplace=True)

# Fill categorical columns with mode
for col in df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns:
    df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0], inplace=True)

# Create Label Encoder for ordinal categories
le = LabelEncoder()

# Label encode traffic_level and priority

priority_map = {'low': 1, 'medium': 2, 'high': 3}

df['traffic_level'] = df['traffic_level'].map(traffic_level_map)
df['priority'] = df['priority'].map(priority_map)

# One-hot encode transport_mode, vehicle_type, and fuel_type
categorical_cols = ['transport_mode', 'vehicle_type', 'fuel_type']
encoded_df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=categorical_cols)

# Verify the encoding
print("Shape after encoding:", encoded_df.shape)
print("\nEncoded columns:", encoded_df.columns)

In[12]:
# Ensure the columns exist in the dataframe before dropping them
columns_to_drop = ['estimated_emissions_kg', 'delivery_point_lat', 'delivery_point_lon', 'package_weight_kg', 'priority', 'transit_time_days', 'transport_mode_air', 'transport_mode_rail', 'transport_mode_ship', 'transport_mode_truck',]
existing_columns_to_drop = [col for col in columns_to_drop if col in data.columns]

# Create new features
data['fuel_efficiency'] = data['distance_km'] / data['fuel_consumed_liters']
data['emission_intensity'] = data['estimated_emissions_kg'] / data['distance_km']

x = data.drop(existing_columns_to_drop, axis=1)
y = data['estimated_emissions_kg']

# Split the data to training and test sets
xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = ts(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
print(xtrain.shape, xtest.shape)

(2894, 16) (724, 16)

    models[i].fit(xtrain, ytrain)

    print(f"\n------{models[i]}--------")

    print("R2" , format(r2_score(ytest,ypred)))

In[15]:
# Initialize lists to store the performance metrics
mae_list = []
r2_list = []
model_names = ['Linear Regression', 'MLP Regressor', 'XGB Regressor', 'Random Forest Regressor']

# Calculate performance metrics for each model
for i in range(4):
    ypred = models[i].predict(xtest)
    mae_list.append(mean_absolute_error(ytest, ypred))
    r2_list.append(r2_score(ytest, ypred))

# Create a dataframe to hold the performance metrics
performance_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Model': model_names,
    'MAE': mae_list,
    'R2': r2_list
})

# Plot the performance metrics
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))

# MAE
plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
sns.barplot(x='Model', y='MAE', data=performance_df)
plt.title('Mean Absolute Error (MAE)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)


# R2
plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
sns.barplot(x='Model', y='R2', data=performance_df)
plt.title('R-squared (R2)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[19]:
# Define hyperparameter search space for XGBoost
param_grid = {
    "max_depth": [3, 5, 8, 10],
    "learning_rate": [0.01, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5,0.8, 1],
}

gs= GridSearchCV(xgb_model, param_grid, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')
gs.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
# print best parameters and tune the model
print(f"Best Parameters: ", gs.best_params_)

r2_list = []

# Calculate performance metrics for each model
for i in range(6):
    y_pred = models[i].predict(x_test)
    mae_list.append(mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred))
    r2_list.append(r2_score(y_test, y_pred))

# Create a dataframe to hold the performance metrics

    'Model': model_names,
    'MAE': mae_list,
    'R2': r2_list

Stacking

In[36]:
from sklearn.ensemble import StackingRegressor

base_learners=[
    ('xgb_model', XGBRegressor(learning_rate=0.1, max_depth=10, n_estimators=200, subsample=1.0)),
    ('rf_model', RandomForestRegressor())
]

# Define the meta model
meta_model= SVR()

#Create Stacking Model
stacking_model=StackingRegressor(estimators=base_learners, final_estimator=meta_model)

#Fit the stacking model
stacking_model.fit(x_train, y_train)

#Predict the values
stacking_pred=stacking_model.predict(x_test)

print("MAE :", mean_absolute_error(y_test, stacking_pred))
print("R2 :", r2_score(y_test, stacking_pred))

MAE : 1.6803158817929245
R2 : 0.5069171588972945

inertia=[]
for k in range(1, 11):
    kmeans=KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)

    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)

# Initialize lists to store the performance metrics
mae_list = []
r2_list = []
model_names = ['Linear Regression', 'MLP Regressor', 'XGB Regressor', 'Random Forest Regressor', 'ElasticNet', 'SVR']

# Calculate performance metrics for each model
for i in range(6):
    ypred_f = models_f[i].predict(xtest_f)
    mae_list.append(mean_absolute_error(ytest_f, ypred_f))
    r2_list.append(r2_score(ytest_f, ypred_f))

# Create a dataframe to hold the performance metrics
performance_d = pd.DataFrame({
    'Model': model_names,
    'MAE': mae_list,
    'R2': r2_list
})

# Plot the performance metrics
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))

# MAE
plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
sns.barplot(x='Model', y='MAE', data=performance_d)
plt.title('Mean Absolute Error (MAE)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)


# R2
plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
sns.barplot(x='Model', y='R2', data=performance_d)
plt.title('R-squared (R2)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Stacking

In[213]:
base_learners=[
    ('xgb_model',  MLPRegressor(hidden_layer_sizes=(11,11,11), learning_rate= 'adaptive', activation='relu', solver='adam', max_iter=1000)),
    ('rf_model', LinearRegression())
]

# Define the meta model
meta_model= SVR()

#Create Stacking Model
stacking_model=StackingRegressor(estimators=base_learners, final_estimator=meta_model)

#Fit the stacking model
stacking_model.fit(xtrain_f, ytrain_f)

#Predict the values
stacking_pred=stacking_model.predict(xtest_f)

print("MAE :", mean_absolute_error(ytest_f, stacking_pred))
print("R2 :", r2_score(ytest_f, stacking_pred))

MAE : 0.39704346435057986
R2 : 0.6313004763895752
